# ZUUP — Demo Refinement Implementation Plan

## Goal

Transform the current simulation into a fully self-explanatory live demo. A first-time viewer must be able to understand the entire bus demand-response system within 2 minutes of watching, without any prior knowledge of the app.

---

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Bidirectional routes**: Each route currently goes A→B. The return journey B→A uses the same road network. Should the return buses be:
> - **Option A**: New buses that start at terminus B and travel back to A (making it truly bidirectional with 6 buses per route showing both directions)  
> - **Option B**: The same buses loop back — when they reach terminus B, they reverse and drive back to A (like a real bus service)
>
> **Recommendation**: Option B is more realistic and avoids spawning too many buses on screen.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Reserve bus count**: How many reserve buses should exist per route? Currently there are 0 in `RESERVE` status. A reserve fleet of 1-2 buses total (parked at a depot stop) would be ideal for the demo. Where should the depot/reserve stop be shown on the map?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Demo speed**: Should the simulation run at realistic speed (10-15 min between buses) or at an accelerated demo speed (buses take ~2-3 minutes to traverse the full route)? Currently the full route takes ~11 minutes at `positionFraction += 0.003` per 2s tick.

