## Edge Cases Covered

| # | Edge Case | Handling |
|---|-----------|----------|
| EC-1 | **No OSRM intersection found** between two routes | Fall back to closest geographic point; if still too far (>500m), bus is ineligible for cross-route rerouting |
| EC-2 | **Reserve bus already in service** when a second surge fires | Reserve treated as IN_SERVICE — skip to Step 5 cross-route reallocation |
| EC-3 | **Bus reaches terminus before intersection** | Bus loops back (bidirectional), recalculate intersection on return leg |
| EC-4 | **Driver rejects reroute instruction** | Cancel reroute order, increment `rerouteRejectionsToday`, escalate alert to Tier 1 |
| EC-5 | **Multiple simultaneous surges** | Each processed independently via `activeProcessing` set; reserve can only be used once |
| EC-6 | **Rerouted bus reaches end of new route** | Bus completes the new route, then returns to `homeRouteId` via natural terminus loop |
| EC-7 | **Surge clears before bus arrives** | `evaluateReserveReturn()` detects demand resolution and sends bus back before it even reaches the stop |
| EC-8 | **All buses REROUTING status** (network deadlock) | RerouteEngine has `cascadeCheck` to prevent this; at least `minBusesInService` buses must remain per route |
| EC-9 | **Hover stop in SimulationPanel with map not loaded** | Guard with null check; highlight queued until map is ready |
| EC-10 | **Return-leg bus at wrong fraction on new route** | Fraction is clamped to [0,1] and validated against route geometry length before assignment |

