2. Wait 10s → Bus 1 departs, drives the route
3. Wait until Bus 1 is at 50% → Bus 2 departs
4. Wait until Bus 2 is at 50% → Bus 3 departs
5. Observe bidirectional lines (both directions visible on map)
6. Hover over stops in SimulationPanel → correct stop pulses on map
7. Inject crowd at a specific stop
8. Observe: Reserve bus dispatched → drives to overloaded stop
9. Wait 90s → demand checker runs → reserve returns to depot (or stays if still needed)
10. If demand too high even with reserve: observe a bus from another route driving to intersection point → transferring to overloaded route naturally
11. After demand clears: transferred bus returns to home route

